1
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:34,918
=Vanished Name=

2
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,556
=Episode 25=
(Calm and Peaceful)

3
00:02:08,626 --> 00:02:10,746
You're here in Qingzhou,
what about Ren Xiaofei?

4
00:02:18,387 --> 00:02:20,107
He worries about you more than I do.

5
00:02:20,906 --> 00:02:21,987
Tell me the truth.

6
00:02:22,827 --> 00:02:24,267
What do you want to do?

7
00:02:27,866 --> 00:02:29,426
Don't stare at me like that.

8
00:02:39,387 --> 00:02:42,067
Alright, just messing with you.
It's fine.

9
00:02:46,947 --> 00:02:47,906
What's wrong?

10
00:02:54,026 --> 00:02:56,827
Rumors say you tried to kill
yourself by taking pills in the US.

11
00:02:57,787 --> 00:02:59,426
Is that true?

12
00:03:01,667 --> 00:03:02,987
I did take pills,

13
00:03:04,426 --> 00:03:05,466
but not to kill myself.

14
00:03:07,186 --> 00:03:08,186
I just took too much.

15
00:03:20,227 --> 00:03:22,787
I'm a suspected mental patient now.
Why do you seem like one?

16
00:03:23,466 --> 00:03:26,746
There's an empty bed there
for you to stay.

17
00:03:30,186 --> 00:03:33,186
I know that incident has always
been hard for you to get over.

18
00:03:37,746 --> 00:03:39,746
When you were in the US back then,

19
00:03:40,586 --> 00:03:41,586
I knew you were abroad,

20
00:03:42,227 --> 00:03:43,448
but the issue wasn't resolved.

21
00:03:45,026 --> 00:03:47,626
We've both been avoiding this topic.

22
00:03:49,267 --> 00:03:50,987
About the thing
between you and He Yuqiong,

23
00:03:52,067 --> 00:03:54,026
do you resent me?

24
00:04:06,787 --> 00:04:08,387
Be honest.

25
00:04:13,987 --> 00:04:17,027
Do you know
why He Yuqiong and I split up?

26
00:04:24,547 --> 00:04:25,707
Because of me?

27
00:04:26,907 --> 00:04:28,186
Don't flatter yourself!

28
00:04:44,978 --> 00:04:46,107
(Spring Festival's Eve, January 25, 2009
Basement rental in Qingzhou)

29
00:04:46,107 --> 00:04:50,826
(Golden Ox heralds the New Year.
Myriad lights celebrate reunion.)

30
00:04:51,467 --> 00:04:53,306
(Dear folks.)

31
00:04:53,547 --> 00:04:55,946
(- Happy Spring Festival!
- Happy Spring Festival!)

32
00:04:57,147 --> 00:05:00,266
(This is the live broadcast site
of the 2009 Spring Festival Gala!)

33
00:05:00,907 --> 00:05:03,066
(As we ring out the old
and ring in the new,)

34
00:05:03,266 --> 00:05:05,027
(we wish you a happy Spring Festival!)

35
00:05:05,746 --> 00:05:08,186
(In 2008, all of us witnessed)

36
00:05:08,186 --> 00:05:10,347
(the Olympic torch ignited passion.)

37
00:05:10,787 --> 00:05:13,946
(And we joined hands to get through
difficult times of earthquake relief.)

38
00:05:14,386 --> 00:05:16,987
(In 2009, let us,
with the resilience of the Golden Ox,)

39
00:05:17,347 --> 00:05:21,426
(forge ahead on the journey of ensuring
growth and improving livelihoods.)

40
00:05:22,066 --> 00:05:25,266
(Brilliant lanterns
play the melody of spring.)

41
00:05:25,667 --> 00:05:29,027
(Joyful songs and laughter
paint a splendid chapter of prosperity.)

42
00:05:29,266 --> 00:05:33,467
(Now enjoy the performance "Splendid
Chapter Welcomes the New Spring".)

43
00:05:38,386 --> 00:05:40,626
Why didn't you tell me you came back?

44
00:05:40,987 --> 00:05:43,506
I went to your place
and found the TV set outside your door,

45
00:05:43,707 --> 00:05:45,066
so I guessed you have come back.

46
00:05:57,506 --> 00:05:59,347
Why are you so cold?

47
00:06:01,186 --> 00:06:02,347
Heavy snow blocked the road.

48
00:06:02,667 --> 00:06:04,347
Without any vehicles, I walked back.

49
00:06:04,547 --> 00:06:05,746
Are you cold?

50
00:06:08,186 --> 00:06:09,787
I worried about you being alone here.

51
00:06:12,547 --> 00:06:14,587
There's only
half a pack of noodles left.

52
00:06:15,547 --> 00:06:18,306
It's okay. I didn't go home either.

53
00:06:18,907 --> 00:06:20,587
I bought two packs on the way.

54
00:06:20,907 --> 00:06:22,746
Just a small token, take it.

55
00:06:25,746 --> 00:06:26,987
And two sausages.

56
00:06:27,266 --> 00:06:28,626
Use the nunchucks!

57
00:06:31,306 --> 00:06:33,208
Let's have
Spring Festival's Eve dinner here.

58
00:07:00,987 --> 00:07:02,147
Sneaking a picture of me?

59
00:07:03,066 --> 00:07:04,347
So what?

60
00:07:14,587 --> 00:07:15,787
Let me see.

61
00:07:19,667 --> 00:07:20,787
I've thought it through.

62
00:07:21,386 --> 00:07:22,946
I can learn a trade.

63
00:07:23,946 --> 00:07:25,107
For example,

64
00:07:27,866 --> 00:07:28,626
cooking.

65
00:07:29,946 --> 00:07:31,547
Everywhere needs chefs, right?

66
00:07:31,866 --> 00:07:33,506
Or driving.

67
00:07:33,987 --> 00:07:37,426
Such a big city
definitely needs lots of drivers.

68
00:07:39,506 --> 00:07:41,066
There are quite a few things I can do.

69
00:07:43,027 --> 00:07:45,506
Life will get better for us, right?

70
00:07:46,746 --> 00:07:49,027
But going back to our hometown
would be much easier.

71
00:07:50,787 --> 00:07:52,866
Why take the easier way?

72
00:07:53,386 --> 00:07:54,587
As the old saying goes,

73
00:07:55,386 --> 00:07:58,787
a person walks steadier
with a load on their back.

74
00:08:03,866 --> 00:08:05,866
Do you know why I came back?

75
00:08:06,587 --> 00:08:07,467
Why?

76
00:08:08,386 --> 00:08:09,987
Because you once said,

77
00:08:11,107 --> 00:08:13,946
as long as the fan keeps spinning,
we won't part ways.

78
00:08:14,467 --> 00:08:15,266
It's cold.

79
00:08:16,266 --> 00:08:17,186
It's cold.

80
00:08:17,506 --> 00:08:18,426
Turn it off.

81
00:08:19,587 --> 00:08:21,907
Give it to me.

82
00:08:22,186 --> 00:08:22,987
Give it to me.

83
00:08:23,266 --> 00:08:25,066
Experience the breeze in cold winter.

84
00:08:26,186 --> 00:08:26,686
Come on.

85
00:08:27,306 --> 00:08:28,066
It's cold.

86
00:08:28,186 --> 00:08:29,147
Don't run away.

87
00:08:29,147 --> 00:08:29,946
It's cold.

88
00:08:30,107 --> 00:08:31,186
Take off your hat.

89
00:08:31,186 --> 00:08:31,826
No!

90
00:08:31,907 --> 00:08:34,947
(- Happy Spring Festival!
- Happy Spring Festival!)

91
00:08:36,506 --> 00:08:39,707
(- Happy Spring Festival!
- Happy Spring Festival!)

92
00:08:46,307 --> 00:08:48,467
- Ten!
- Nine!

93
00:08:48,906 --> 00:08:50,626
- Eight!
- Seven!

94
00:08:50,746 --> 00:08:51,626
Six!

95
00:08:51,827 --> 00:08:52,506
(Happy Spring Festival)
Five!

96
00:08:52,626 --> 00:08:54,146
- Four!
- Three!

97
00:08:54,227 --> 00:08:55,626
- Two!
- One!

98
00:08:55,626 --> 00:08:58,546
Happy Spring Festival!

99
00:09:41,666 --> 00:09:43,146
Here, take this.

100
00:09:44,026 --> 00:09:44,987
It's your payment.

101
00:09:45,746 --> 00:09:46,467
Thanks, Mr. Liu.

102
00:09:46,666 --> 00:09:48,906
Not at all. Professor Zhuang
has been praising you.

103
00:09:49,067 --> 00:09:52,827
He says you're hardworking, diligent,
and smart. You're a promising student.

104
00:09:53,026 --> 00:09:55,587
You'll definitely pass the exam
to be his graduate student.

105
00:09:55,987 --> 00:09:57,347
Then let me treat you to a meal.

106
00:09:57,386 --> 00:09:58,506
What for?

107
00:09:58,506 --> 00:10:00,546
Come on, Professor Zhuang
is treating us to a meal.

108
00:10:00,707 --> 00:10:03,067
At the table,
I'll put in a good word for you.

109
00:10:03,626 --> 00:10:04,126
Let's go.

110
00:10:04,626 --> 00:10:06,187
I might not go to the meal.

111
00:10:06,347 --> 00:10:07,347
Why?

112
00:10:07,546 --> 00:10:08,347
Remember,

113
00:10:08,866 --> 00:10:11,386
university relationships
are important social resources.

114
00:10:11,386 --> 00:10:12,827
Learn how to network effectively

115
00:10:13,107 --> 00:10:14,187
and seize the opportunity.

116
00:10:14,786 --> 00:10:15,626
Trust me. Let's go.

117
00:10:16,347 --> 00:10:17,146
Let's go.

118
00:10:19,746 --> 00:10:21,107
I heard you're leaving next month.

119
00:10:22,067 --> 00:10:25,187
Yes, classes will start
in the US in August.

120
00:10:25,506 --> 00:10:27,107
- I'm going early in July.
- Xiao...

121
00:10:27,307 --> 00:10:29,227
To get familiar
with the environment in advance.

122
00:10:29,587 --> 00:10:30,347
That's great.

123
00:10:31,026 --> 00:10:32,506
Do you have plans to study abroad?

124
00:10:32,666 --> 00:10:34,067
My family can't afford it.

125
00:10:35,026 --> 00:10:36,266
You can get a scholarship.

126
00:10:36,626 --> 00:10:38,347
I can help you with that.

127
00:10:38,866 --> 00:10:39,866
Can I get one?

128
00:10:40,307 --> 00:10:43,866
Passing the exam shouldn't be a problem
for a student from our university.

129
00:10:44,187 --> 00:10:46,386
The key is whether
you want to study abroad.

130
00:10:47,307 --> 00:10:47,827
I want to.

131
00:10:48,307 --> 00:10:48,906
That's good.

132
00:10:49,227 --> 00:10:51,067
If you want to, then there's a way.

133
00:10:52,746 --> 00:10:54,266
I'll think about it.

134
00:10:55,546 --> 00:10:57,746
The delivery guy has kept me waiting.

135
00:10:57,746 --> 00:10:58,707
Such a long time.

136
00:10:59,506 --> 00:11:01,587
I ordered two servings
of egg fried rice long ago.

137
00:11:01,687 --> 00:11:02,187
So slow.

138
00:11:02,187 --> 00:11:03,187
You lay the eggs?

139
00:11:03,386 --> 00:11:04,107
Sorry about that.

140
00:11:04,107 --> 00:11:04,786
Way too slow.

141
00:11:05,067 --> 00:11:06,227
I will give you a discount.

142
00:11:07,107 --> 00:11:09,506
It is cold now.
How am I supposed to eat it?

143
00:11:09,866 --> 00:11:10,866
Keep it for yourself.

144
00:11:10,866 --> 00:11:11,546
You eat it.

145
00:11:13,546 --> 00:11:14,227
Pick them up.

146
00:11:16,067 --> 00:11:16,626
What?

147
00:11:17,906 --> 00:11:18,987
Who do you think you are?

148
00:11:19,266 --> 00:11:19,947
Pick them up.

149
00:11:20,187 --> 00:11:21,146
You pick them up.

150
00:11:35,626 --> 00:11:36,987
Off work so early today?

151
00:11:40,107 --> 00:11:40,827
I quit.

152
00:11:44,347 --> 00:11:45,227
What happened again?

153
00:11:45,947 --> 00:11:46,827
Again?

154
00:11:48,467 --> 00:11:50,386
You haven't been in Qingzhou for long.

155
00:11:51,026 --> 00:11:52,107
You've changed jobs twice.

156
00:11:54,266 --> 00:11:57,307
None lasted long. I'm not wrong.

157
00:12:01,746 --> 00:12:04,746
Hold on. What's wrong? You're bleeding.

158
00:12:06,947 --> 00:12:08,187
Did you get in a fight?

159
00:12:08,626 --> 00:12:09,266
Sit.

160
00:12:17,626 --> 00:12:18,786
Where else are you hurt?

161
00:12:21,026 --> 00:12:22,187
Wait, I'll clean it.

162
00:12:26,467 --> 00:12:28,386
Sit there and don't move.

163
00:12:43,707 --> 00:12:44,707
What's wrong with you?

164
00:12:46,307 --> 00:12:47,786
Why vent your anger at me?

165
00:12:49,386 --> 00:12:51,067
Did you lose your job
because of the fight?

166
00:12:52,746 --> 00:12:53,906
Why vent your anger at me?

167
00:12:54,746 --> 00:12:55,746
Did I tell you to fight?

168
00:13:02,107 --> 00:13:03,746
If you have a lunch gathering,

169
00:13:03,746 --> 00:13:04,987
just let me know in advance.

170
00:13:07,386 --> 00:13:09,187
You went to bring me food?

171
00:13:09,866 --> 00:13:11,107
I forgot it.

172
00:13:13,467 --> 00:13:14,347
It's fine.

173
00:13:15,187 --> 00:13:16,067
He Yuqiong.

174
00:13:16,827 --> 00:13:18,587
It's just one meal. Is it a big deal?

175
00:13:58,546 --> 00:14:01,187
I'm sorry. I spoke too harshly just now.

176
00:14:01,906 --> 00:14:04,146
I was wrong. I shouldn't have
spoken to you like that.

177
00:14:04,347 --> 00:14:05,666
Don't be mad anymore, okay?

178
00:14:07,227 --> 00:14:10,587
If my plans change,
I'll definitely tell you in advance.

179
00:14:11,347 --> 00:14:14,947
I really didn't mean to.
There was too much going on yesterday.

180
00:14:15,067 --> 00:14:16,947
I really forgot it.

181
00:14:18,467 --> 00:14:20,187
Don't be mad at me.

182
00:14:25,067 --> 00:14:27,786
I got my payment today.
I'll treat you to something good.

183
00:14:27,947 --> 00:14:29,587
What's wrong?

184
00:14:33,546 --> 00:14:35,587
I'll treat you to something good, okay?

185
00:14:37,786 --> 00:14:39,506
Don't cry. It hurts me.

186
00:14:44,467 --> 00:14:46,827
Tell me why you got in a fight.

187
00:14:47,347 --> 00:14:48,506
Did they bully you?

188
00:14:48,746 --> 00:14:50,707
It must be their fault. It's not on you.

189
00:14:50,707 --> 00:14:52,067
Tell me, why did you fight?

190
00:14:53,587 --> 00:14:54,746
Did you fight?

191
00:15:05,827 --> 00:15:06,906
What's wrong?

192
00:15:13,227 --> 00:15:14,786
As soon as you graduate, we'll...

193
00:15:23,067 --> 00:15:24,546
It's Mr. Liu. I need to take this.

194
00:15:26,906 --> 00:15:27,786
Mr. Liu?

195
00:15:29,187 --> 00:15:30,266
I'm not busy. What's up?

196
00:15:32,707 --> 00:15:33,467
Wrong?

197
00:15:33,967 --> 00:15:35,467
Okay, then. I-I'll go fix it.

198
00:15:36,587 --> 00:15:37,866
Now? Okay.

199
00:15:38,386 --> 00:15:39,786
The cafe, right? Okay.

200
00:15:40,707 --> 00:15:42,746
Wait for me. See you soon. Bye.

201
00:15:45,386 --> 00:15:46,906
I need to go.

202
00:15:47,307 --> 00:15:49,947
The data I worked on was wrong.

203
00:15:49,947 --> 00:15:52,587
I need to go fix it. I'll be back soon.

204
00:15:52,906 --> 00:15:54,786
I'll bring you something good, okay?

205
00:15:55,906 --> 00:15:57,112
Come on.

206
00:15:58,296 --> 00:16:01,506
Don't look so upset. Don't be mad.

207
00:16:01,746 --> 00:16:03,107
Tell me you're not mad anymore.

208
00:16:03,707 --> 00:16:05,906
Then I'm going. I'm going.

209
00:16:10,546 --> 00:16:12,987
Give me a smile, okay?

210
00:16:14,146 --> 00:16:16,467
That smile looks awful.
Give me a real one.

211
00:16:17,906 --> 00:16:18,707
Smile.

212
00:16:22,227 --> 00:16:24,026
I'm going now. Be good.

213
00:16:32,146 --> 00:16:32,746
I need to go.

214
00:16:33,707 --> 00:16:34,227
Bye.

215
00:17:18,427 --> 00:17:19,147
Mr. Liu.

216
00:17:21,266 --> 00:17:23,387
I'm here. What do I need to change?

217
00:17:23,546 --> 00:17:25,786
Drink this first.
I didn't order coffee for you.

218
00:17:26,187 --> 00:17:27,586
It doesn't contain tea polyphenols.

219
00:17:27,707 --> 00:17:29,627
It'll perk you up
without affecting your sleep.

220
00:17:30,187 --> 00:17:31,746
Thanks, Mr. Liu. Water is fine for me.

221
00:17:32,106 --> 00:17:33,306
No need to thank me.

222
00:17:33,427 --> 00:17:36,026
You're helping me out.
It's only right I take care of you.

223
00:17:37,346 --> 00:17:38,506
So, what needs changing?

224
00:17:39,306 --> 00:17:42,026
See? We used the wrong formula.

225
00:17:42,187 --> 00:17:43,467
That caused data in this column,

226
00:17:44,187 --> 00:17:46,506
all the way to the end, to be wrong.

227
00:17:48,387 --> 00:17:51,266
We must finish
these hundreds of survey forms tonight.

228
00:17:52,346 --> 00:17:54,907
No problem.
Give them to me, I'll handle it.

229
00:17:55,947 --> 00:17:56,987
Wait, this...

230
00:17:58,106 --> 00:17:58,987
To change the data.

231
00:17:59,187 --> 00:17:59,867
All of them?

232
00:18:00,106 --> 00:18:01,147
I'm here to supervise?

233
00:18:01,227 --> 00:18:02,427
I'm here to work too.

234
00:18:02,746 --> 00:18:03,947
We should split it.

235
00:18:05,106 --> 00:18:05,627
Take these.

236
00:18:05,627 --> 00:18:06,427
- Here.
- No, no.

237
00:18:06,427 --> 00:18:07,147
Give me more.

238
00:18:07,147 --> 00:18:08,026
Enough. Alright.

239
00:18:08,026 --> 00:18:08,546
Okay.

240
00:18:08,546 --> 00:18:09,627
You start. Get to work.

241
00:18:09,627 --> 00:18:10,346
Okay, fine.

242
00:18:15,427 --> 00:18:17,506
See? Start from here.

243
00:18:18,627 --> 00:18:19,546
The first page.

244
00:18:19,907 --> 00:18:20,467
Right.

245
00:18:26,026 --> 00:18:26,786
From here,

246
00:18:27,987 --> 00:18:28,907
all the way to the end.

247
00:18:29,026 --> 00:18:29,627
All of them.

248
00:18:29,707 --> 00:18:30,346
Right here.

249
00:18:30,346 --> 00:18:30,867
Okay.

250
00:18:34,266 --> 00:18:36,306
I didn't finish my words
when I dropped you off.

251
00:18:36,427 --> 00:18:39,066
Why did you suddenly refuse
to go abroad?

252
00:18:40,387 --> 00:18:41,506
I have a boyfriend.

253
00:18:44,026 --> 00:18:45,306
Don't tell others.

254
00:18:51,987 --> 00:18:52,627
Why?

255
00:18:54,266 --> 00:18:56,147
Maybe it's because I'm a vain woman.

256
00:18:57,467 --> 00:18:58,907
I always feel like if I tell others

257
00:18:58,907 --> 00:19:00,586
my boyfriend is from my hometown,

258
00:19:01,387 --> 00:19:04,266
it might seem a bit embarrassing.

259
00:19:08,627 --> 00:19:10,586
The fact that you can say about it

260
00:19:10,786 --> 00:19:12,346
shows you're not a vain woman.

261
00:19:14,387 --> 00:19:16,987
Actually, things like dating

262
00:19:16,987 --> 00:19:20,627
are personal.
There's no need to tell others, right?

263
00:19:23,106 --> 00:19:24,907
So, is he

264
00:19:26,506 --> 00:19:27,546
against you going abroad?

265
00:19:29,467 --> 00:19:31,467
No, he supports me.

266
00:19:32,066 --> 00:19:33,667
Whatever I do, he supports me.

267
00:19:36,427 --> 00:19:37,627
It's mainly because

268
00:19:39,106 --> 00:19:40,227
he isn't highly educated.

269
00:19:41,026 --> 00:19:42,506
Well, in a place like Qingzhou,

270
00:19:42,506 --> 00:19:45,147
finding a job and making a living
is hard enough.

271
00:19:45,387 --> 00:19:46,947
Going abroad is even harder, right?

272
00:19:48,227 --> 00:19:51,106
I don't want him to suffer more for me.

273
00:19:53,187 --> 00:19:53,707
Why...

274
00:19:53,707 --> 00:19:54,826
- Give it to me.
- It's fine.

275
00:19:54,826 --> 00:19:56,387
- It's okay, let me.
- Put your bag here.

276
00:19:56,387 --> 00:19:57,506
No. It's fine.

277
00:19:57,546 --> 00:19:59,667
It's not dirty.

278
00:19:59,846 --> 00:20:01,227
Alright, just put it here.

279
00:20:01,246 --> 00:20:02,246
Okay. Sure.

280
00:20:02,786 --> 00:20:03,987
No problem.

281
00:20:07,306 --> 00:20:08,746
You really care about him.

282
00:20:10,306 --> 00:20:11,746
I adore him.

283
00:20:12,266 --> 00:20:15,106
I thought about marrying him
right after graduation.

284
00:20:16,147 --> 00:20:16,987
Getting married?

285
00:20:17,407 --> 00:20:19,627
Yes, I can get married
while learning in grad school.

286
00:20:20,227 --> 00:20:23,506
After I finish grad school,

287
00:20:23,826 --> 00:20:25,586
I'll find a higher-paying job.

288
00:20:25,786 --> 00:20:27,707
Then, he won't have
to be exhausted in working.

289
00:20:37,907 --> 00:20:39,387
Have you considered one thing?

290
00:20:39,987 --> 00:20:41,707
Then you'll be the one
exhausted in working.

291
00:20:44,947 --> 00:20:45,987
No.

292
00:20:46,786 --> 00:20:48,387
I think two people working hard

293
00:20:48,826 --> 00:20:50,147
for each other isn't exhausted,

294
00:20:52,266 --> 00:20:53,667
but happiness.

295
00:20:58,707 --> 00:20:59,467
That's great.

296
00:21:00,867 --> 00:21:01,707
I envy you guys.

297
00:21:05,427 --> 00:21:06,106
Tell me,

298
00:21:06,106 --> 00:21:08,346
what tricks did he use to win you over?

299
00:21:09,987 --> 00:21:11,627
No tricks.

300
00:21:12,987 --> 00:21:14,306
Tell me about it.

301
00:21:15,586 --> 00:21:17,026
I don't know either.

302
00:21:18,746 --> 00:21:20,387
I guess I'm used to it.

303
00:21:20,987 --> 00:21:22,346
And,

304
00:21:22,707 --> 00:21:25,147
I don't know why, every time
I think about him, I feel happy

305
00:21:25,707 --> 00:21:26,627
and can't help smiling.

306
00:21:26,907 --> 00:21:28,786
I feel really happy when I'm with him.

307
00:21:30,266 --> 00:21:32,227
Even now,
thinking about him makes you smile?

308
00:21:35,546 --> 00:21:37,106
I can feel your happiness.

309
00:21:40,066 --> 00:21:42,667
But in my point of view,

310
00:21:44,266 --> 00:21:45,667
it's a pity.

311
00:21:46,867 --> 00:21:49,667
You could have gone much further.

312
00:21:51,746 --> 00:21:53,147
Actually, I've thought about

313
00:21:53,627 --> 00:21:55,266
going out to experience the world.

314
00:21:56,147 --> 00:21:58,467
But one can't have it all.

315
00:21:59,106 --> 00:22:00,387
How far I can go

316
00:22:00,667 --> 00:22:03,826
isn't just about me, right?

317
00:22:03,987 --> 00:22:05,627
I have to consider my partner.

318
00:22:07,546 --> 00:22:08,346
I think,

319
00:22:09,586 --> 00:22:11,826
I've decided to be

320
00:22:12,266 --> 00:22:13,427
with him,

321
00:22:13,987 --> 00:22:15,707
so I have to stick with it.

322
00:22:16,947 --> 00:22:20,387
No matter what, we should support
each other and keep moving forward.

323
00:22:30,427 --> 00:22:31,786
What's up, Mr. Liu?

324
00:22:32,346 --> 00:22:33,427
Nothing, it's fine.

325
00:22:34,066 --> 00:22:34,987
Wishing you happiness.

326
00:22:35,346 --> 00:22:36,266
Thank you.

327
00:22:37,786 --> 00:22:40,427
Mr. Liu, could you take a look at this?

328
00:22:42,066 --> 00:22:45,227
I've already updated
this part of the form.

329
00:22:46,867 --> 00:22:48,467
This part is all fixed.

330
00:22:48,467 --> 00:22:52,066
But I feel changing this part
might cause issues here.

331
00:22:52,586 --> 00:22:53,227
Okay.

332
00:23:09,026 --> 00:23:10,506
It smells amazing!

333
00:23:11,306 --> 00:23:12,227
Hot pot?

334
00:23:12,586 --> 00:23:13,306
Yes.

335
00:23:13,306 --> 00:23:14,266
Did you get potatoes?

336
00:23:14,266 --> 00:23:15,026
Yes.

337
00:23:15,387 --> 00:23:16,346
Cheese balls?

338
00:23:16,467 --> 00:23:18,306
Absolutely, I already dropped them in.

339
00:23:21,066 --> 00:23:22,467
You are so wonderful.

340
00:23:29,187 --> 00:23:30,066
It smells amazing!

341
00:23:37,187 --> 00:23:38,066
Why aren't you eating?

342
00:23:38,907 --> 00:23:40,227
Let's have a talk.

343
00:23:40,346 --> 00:23:40,846
Go ahead.

344
00:23:42,387 --> 00:23:43,907
I want to go back to Qidaohezi.

345
00:23:44,867 --> 00:23:45,707
Why?

346
00:23:49,667 --> 00:23:51,187
I just don't want to stay here.

347
00:23:55,707 --> 00:23:56,746
Why not?

348
00:23:58,586 --> 00:24:01,227
Jobs are hard to find here,
and the cost of living is high.

349
00:24:03,867 --> 00:24:05,227
Staying here is exhausting.

350
00:24:05,987 --> 00:24:06,627
I...

351
00:24:07,227 --> 00:24:10,346
I graduate in two years.
Can you hold on a bit longer?

352
00:24:11,066 --> 00:24:12,947
You'll take the grad school
after graduation.

353
00:24:13,467 --> 00:24:15,026
I'd only distract you from studying.

354
00:24:15,306 --> 00:24:16,707
Not at all.

355
00:24:20,707 --> 00:24:22,187
I want to take the grad school

356
00:24:22,786 --> 00:24:24,786
to find a better job after graduation.

357
00:24:26,746 --> 00:24:29,746
That way, life will be easier for us
after we get married.

358
00:24:30,306 --> 00:24:30,867
Exactly.

359
00:24:32,227 --> 00:24:35,987
If we're getting together,
you'll have to support the family.

360
00:24:37,746 --> 00:24:39,667
What do you mean?

361
00:24:40,586 --> 00:24:41,826
What? You forgot it?

362
00:24:42,346 --> 00:24:43,987
You promised me to buy me a big house.

363
00:24:44,427 --> 00:24:45,987
You said to be the next Buffett?

364
00:24:50,346 --> 00:24:52,746
Your sausage stand
is doing pretty well, isn't it?

365
00:24:53,026 --> 00:24:54,586
Don't rush. Just take it step by step.

366
00:24:55,306 --> 00:24:56,667
Just make a plan, okay?

367
00:24:57,266 --> 00:24:58,026
Start with

368
00:24:59,586 --> 00:25:01,227
dominating the Qingzhou night market.

369
00:25:06,227 --> 00:25:08,667
You think the night market
is a real career?

370
00:25:09,066 --> 00:25:10,227
What's wrong with that?

371
00:25:10,786 --> 00:25:11,987
My mom is a bath scrubber.

372
00:25:11,987 --> 00:25:13,987
What? Think that's not a real career?

373
00:25:14,467 --> 00:25:16,707
I think you're quite optimistic.

374
00:25:19,467 --> 00:25:22,427
Why have you never introduced me
to your classmates or friends?

375
00:25:26,867 --> 00:25:29,240
That day at the night market,
you were with your roommates.

376
00:25:30,106 --> 00:25:31,427
You saw me, right?

377
00:25:32,947 --> 00:25:33,987
I saw you too.

378
00:25:36,106 --> 00:25:37,627
We both know that.

379
00:25:38,746 --> 00:25:40,664
That's because I told
my classmates you have

380
00:25:40,746 --> 00:25:43,586
a high-paying job at a state-owned
company and a big house.

381
00:25:44,147 --> 00:25:46,546
What if they saw you weren't like that?

382
00:25:50,106 --> 00:25:52,867
It's me being vain. I'm sorry.

383
00:25:53,947 --> 00:25:55,066
No need.

384
00:25:57,467 --> 00:25:59,187
I've put myself in your shoes, really.

385
00:26:02,227 --> 00:26:03,266
I'm quite embarrassing.

386
00:26:04,187 --> 00:26:05,826
Not at all.

387
00:26:10,026 --> 00:26:12,387
When you came to me
on Spring Festival's Eve, I realized

388
00:26:12,387 --> 00:26:14,667
we're going to get married
and have kids.

389
00:26:14,987 --> 00:26:16,627
We're not going to part ways.

390
00:26:21,066 --> 00:26:23,187
- I'll take you to my roommates.
- I want to ask you something.

391
00:26:23,187 --> 00:26:24,627
After the Spring Festival,

392
00:26:25,266 --> 00:26:26,147
you stayed with me.

393
00:26:28,907 --> 00:26:31,627
Were you just using me
to get back at your mom?

394
00:26:32,227 --> 00:26:34,066
He Yuqiong, you're going too far.

395
00:26:34,387 --> 00:26:37,346
Do you really think I'd use our love
just to get back at my mom?

396
00:26:38,387 --> 00:26:39,467
Do you think I'd do that?

397
00:26:44,467 --> 00:26:45,586
That day, I told you

398
00:26:46,867 --> 00:26:48,306
not to stay with me.

399
00:26:49,947 --> 00:26:52,746
Actually, I didn't mean it.
I wanted you to stay with me.

400
00:26:55,467 --> 00:26:59,026
But I was afraid you wouldn't adapt
or get used to life in Qingzhou,

401
00:26:59,667 --> 00:27:01,147
and you'd suffer.

402
00:27:01,147 --> 00:27:03,384
I was worried you couldn't
handle my mom's cold shoulder.

403
00:27:08,627 --> 00:27:09,707
I'm sorry.

404
00:27:16,306 --> 00:27:19,147
I was afraid
you couldn't handle your mom.

405
00:27:32,867 --> 00:27:34,106
I'm sorry.

406
00:27:35,667 --> 00:27:36,786
I'm sorry.

407
00:27:38,907 --> 00:27:39,746
Stop crying.

408
00:27:42,707 --> 00:27:44,667
So, are you staying?

409
00:27:47,746 --> 00:27:49,026
Eat first.

410
00:27:49,026 --> 00:27:50,546
It's all cooked down.

411
00:27:50,707 --> 00:27:53,667
Look, isn't it all cooked down?

412
00:27:56,346 --> 00:27:56,987
Stop crying.

413
00:27:56,987 --> 00:27:57,826
Then sit.

414
00:28:10,306 --> 00:28:12,427
The potatoes are all mushy.

415
00:28:13,467 --> 00:28:14,346
Eat this.

416
00:28:18,187 --> 00:28:19,266
What's wrong?

417
00:28:19,346 --> 00:28:20,786
Just looking at you.

418
00:28:30,786 --> 00:28:31,707
What's wrong, Mom?

419
00:28:34,427 --> 00:28:35,546
Say something.

420
00:28:42,546 --> 00:28:43,346
I got it.

421
00:28:49,506 --> 00:28:50,306
What's wrong?

422
00:28:55,187 --> 00:28:56,627
He Youliang is sick.

423
00:28:59,586 --> 00:29:00,947
Do you go back and see him?

424
00:29:01,387 --> 00:29:02,826
I need to go back to Qidaohezi.

425
00:29:49,586 --> 00:29:50,826
Let me tell you something

426
00:29:51,066 --> 00:29:52,026
about my boyfriend.

427
00:29:55,026 --> 00:29:56,586
My boyfriend's name is He Yuqiong.

428
00:29:58,586 --> 00:30:01,112
We were junior high school classmates.
He's my childhood friend.

429
00:30:02,826 --> 00:30:04,147
He is also my first love.

430
00:30:07,026 --> 00:30:08,696
He hasn't worked
in a state-owned company.

431
00:30:09,346 --> 00:30:12,907
He just lost his food delivery job
a few days ago.

432
00:30:13,707 --> 00:30:16,346
These days, he's selling sausages
at the night market.

433
00:30:17,147 --> 00:30:18,346
He doesn't have any relatives

434
00:30:19,546 --> 00:30:21,266
or a two-bedroom apartment here.

435
00:30:24,346 --> 00:30:25,826
He rented a basement room

436
00:30:27,506 --> 00:30:29,266
less than twenty square meters.

437
00:30:33,467 --> 00:30:34,546
He didn't go to college.

438
00:30:35,867 --> 00:30:37,987
He lacks connections and money.

439
00:30:40,867 --> 00:30:41,947
But he treats me very well.

440
00:30:46,506 --> 00:30:47,387
He's a nice person

441
00:30:49,907 --> 00:30:50,786
and very ambitious.

442
00:30:54,026 --> 00:30:55,106
I think we

443
00:30:57,387 --> 00:30:58,506
will have a bright future.

444
00:31:08,147 --> 00:31:09,947
That's great. You finally said it.

445
00:31:10,506 --> 00:31:13,907
Actually, we've known it
and just didn't dare to bring it up.

446
00:31:19,987 --> 00:31:21,546
I'm sorry.

447
00:31:22,627 --> 00:31:23,907
I didn't dare tell you.

448
00:31:23,907 --> 00:31:25,867
I didn't mean to deceive you.

449
00:31:26,746 --> 00:31:29,467
I was afraid you'd look down on me.

450
00:31:30,306 --> 00:31:31,987
Had I known you knew it,

451
00:31:32,026 --> 00:31:34,106
I would've said it sooner.

452
00:31:38,907 --> 00:31:40,506
It feels much better now.

453
00:31:50,506 --> 00:31:51,627
Thank you.

454
00:31:56,546 --> 00:31:57,266
I'm done.

455
00:31:59,427 --> 00:31:59,987
Split up.

456
00:32:02,387 --> 00:32:02,987
Come on.

457
00:32:14,707 --> 00:32:15,306
(Bai Shu.)

458
00:32:15,867 --> 00:32:18,227
(I did something really brave today.)

459
00:32:18,786 --> 00:32:20,546
(I tore through my own lie.)

460
00:32:21,707 --> 00:32:25,026
(If Ms. Zhou knew, she'd
throw an apple at me and say,)

461
00:32:26,106 --> 00:32:28,506
("Ren Xiaoming, you're amazing.")

462
00:32:37,987 --> 00:32:40,506
A stroke. His liver is failing too.

463
00:32:42,106 --> 00:32:45,066
The doctor said
it's just a matter of time.

464
00:32:47,026 --> 00:32:48,427
Drinking so much in these years,

465
00:32:50,227 --> 00:32:51,627
he gets what he deserves now.

466
00:32:59,707 --> 00:33:00,427
It's okay.

467
00:33:02,546 --> 00:33:03,427
Mom,

468
00:33:05,227 --> 00:33:06,026
you've got me.

469
00:33:11,786 --> 00:33:12,506
Don't cry.

470
00:33:52,546 --> 00:33:54,667
(He Yuqiong has been gone
for over a month.)

471
00:33:56,746 --> 00:33:59,346
(I'm increasingly feeling
he'll never come back.)

472
00:35:03,546 --> 00:35:04,347
Are you hungry?

473
00:35:07,186 --> 00:35:08,427
I'm only back for one day

474
00:35:10,267 --> 00:35:11,387
to say goodbye to you.

475
00:35:14,506 --> 00:35:19,066
Since coming to Qingzhou,
I feel like a robot.

476
00:35:20,467 --> 00:35:21,267
Quite exhausted.

477
00:35:23,907 --> 00:35:24,867
Emotionally exhausted.

478
00:35:26,747 --> 00:35:29,987
I haven't saved money
or taken good care of you.

479
00:35:32,546 --> 00:35:33,907
I ended up doing nothing well.

480
00:35:42,186 --> 00:35:44,867
I said a lot of hurtful things before.

481
00:35:45,387 --> 00:35:47,146
I hurt your self-esteem.

482
00:35:47,787 --> 00:35:48,907
I am sorry.

483
00:35:49,827 --> 00:35:50,787
It's not your fault.

484
00:35:52,987 --> 00:35:55,226
I can't always expect you
to understand me.

485
00:35:57,307 --> 00:35:58,867
I'm not suited for Qingzhou.

486
00:35:59,987 --> 00:36:01,506
Not right.

487
00:36:02,347 --> 00:36:04,146
There's nothing to deny.

488
00:36:04,947 --> 00:36:06,626
You didn't hurt my self-esteem.

489
00:36:09,226 --> 00:36:12,106
You asked if I want to stay with you.

490
00:36:12,827 --> 00:36:13,787
I've thought it through.

491
00:36:15,347 --> 00:36:16,226
I won't do it anymore.

492
00:36:17,307 --> 00:36:19,226
Everyone has different life stages,

493
00:36:19,467 --> 00:36:20,787
and different paths to go.

494
00:36:24,146 --> 00:36:26,106
We're not on the same path.

495
00:36:30,427 --> 00:36:32,186
You're wrong. If not,

496
00:36:32,186 --> 00:36:33,666
then why can I hold you now?

497
00:36:35,186 --> 00:36:36,787
Because you've been accommodating me.

498
00:36:37,427 --> 00:36:38,666
No.

499
00:36:46,666 --> 00:36:49,267
Could we try once more?

500
00:36:50,186 --> 00:36:51,226
Just once.

501
00:36:52,586 --> 00:36:53,666
I want to go back.

502
00:36:54,626 --> 00:36:56,307
Can't you stay for me?

503
00:36:57,626 --> 00:36:59,066
There's no point in staying.

504
00:36:59,347 --> 00:37:01,146
I can't take care of you properly.

505
00:37:01,267 --> 00:37:03,032
Then I'll go back to Qidaohezi with you.

506
00:37:03,347 --> 00:37:05,706
Fine. You come back with me,

507
00:37:07,747 --> 00:37:09,787
and all your years of hard work
will be wasted.

508
00:37:10,987 --> 00:37:12,467
You'll regret it.

509
00:37:13,026 --> 00:37:14,186
You'll resent me.

510
00:37:14,307 --> 00:37:15,626
And because of your resentment,

511
00:37:15,626 --> 00:37:17,546
I might turn into someone like my dad,
drinking and hitting.

512
00:37:17,546 --> 00:37:19,467
We'll both get worse

513
00:37:19,626 --> 00:37:21,307
and end up hating each other.

514
00:37:24,226 --> 00:37:27,427
You focus on studying hard now,
ace that TOEFL,

515
00:37:28,907 --> 00:37:30,947
strive to go abroad and see the world.

516
00:37:32,226 --> 00:37:32,867
Okay?

517
00:37:36,947 --> 00:37:38,347
You knew it?

518
00:37:41,467 --> 00:37:44,347
I knew the girl I chose
would be the best.

519
00:37:45,666 --> 00:37:48,947
Don't set an endpoint for yourself,
and just run forward as hard as you can.

520
00:37:49,267 --> 00:37:51,186
Run as far as you can!

521
00:37:52,586 --> 00:37:54,387
You know I am bad at directions.

522
00:37:55,226 --> 00:37:56,267
What if I get lost?

523
00:37:56,947 --> 00:37:58,506
Then just turn around and look.

524
00:37:59,546 --> 00:38:01,787
I'll be your reference point
at the starting line.

525
00:38:06,787 --> 00:38:09,307
I don't want that.
I want you to come with me.

526
00:38:09,827 --> 00:38:11,787
How can you be so selfish?

527
00:38:12,267 --> 00:38:14,867
You fly in a plane and expect me
to run barefoot after you?

528
00:38:15,626 --> 00:38:17,267
I don't want that.

529
00:38:20,467 --> 00:38:21,307
Enough.

530
00:38:24,467 --> 00:38:25,586
Enough.

531
00:38:26,546 --> 00:38:27,867
Let's stop crying, okay?

532
00:38:32,586 --> 00:38:34,827
Let's make a bet, just one bet.

533
00:38:35,747 --> 00:38:36,666
Bet on what?

534
00:38:43,706 --> 00:38:45,586
(I'm going
to the fireworks testing ground.)

535
00:38:47,026 --> 00:38:48,666
(If they set off fireworks,)

536
00:38:49,146 --> 00:38:50,467
(then we won't break up.)

537
00:39:22,747 --> 00:39:24,106
Ren Xiaoming!

538
00:39:27,706 --> 00:39:28,787
Ren Xiaoming!

539
00:39:29,106 --> 00:39:30,546
I want to see the fireworks!

540
00:39:30,586 --> 00:39:31,347
Ren Xiaoming!

541
00:39:31,747 --> 00:39:32,827
Ren Xiaoming!

542
00:39:33,347 --> 00:39:34,427
Ren Xiaoming!

543
